(52, 'index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=16', 'index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=16:what-we-do&catid=2', 'What we do ', ' At Bet\'eseb Nonprofit Art Center, we are dedicated to promoting art, creativity, and community engagement. With nine years of experience in organizing painting events for all ages, our diverse range of offerings includes: Art Education: Offering diverse art education programs and workshops for all ages and skill levels, fostering artistic growth and inspiring creativity. Community Outreach and Painting Events: Organizing interactive painting events that bring people of all ages and backgrounds together, encouraging creative expression and connection. Traditional Craft Making: Preserve and promote traditional crafts by providing workshops and programs where participants can learn and engage in traditional craft-making techniques, ensuring cultural heritage is passed down to future generations. Traditional Dance: Celebrating cultural diversity through traditional dance workshops and performances, providing opportunities for individuals to learn and embrace various dance forms from different cultures. Heritage Awareness Programs: Raising awareness and appreciation for cultural heritage through educational initiatives, exhibitions, and community projects that explore and showcase the rich history and traditions of our community. Artist Support: Providing opportunities for emerging artists to showcase their work through exhibitions and online platforms. Art Events and Fundraisers: Hosting engaging art events and fundraisers to raise awareness and support our mission. Collaborations: Seeking partnerships with like-minded individuals, businesses, and organizations to expand our reach and impact. ', '2023-06-07 02:40:16', '65c417faa868e0052c7fcc59be69e8ca', 1, 1, 1, '*', '2023-04-04 03:53:27', NULL, '2023-04-04 03:53:27', NULL, 0, 0, 3, ),
(53, 'index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=17', 'index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=17:support-us&catid=2', 'Support Us ', ' Join us in creating an inclusive artistic space where creativity thrives and cultural heritage is celebrated. Here\'s how you can help: Volunteer: Share your time and expertise to assist with events and workshops. Donate: Support our art education programs and emerging artists with a generous contribution. Sponsorship: Collaborate with us to showcase your brand and support our mission. Spread the Word: Share our website and events with your network. Attend: Join us at our art events, workshops, and exhibitions. For more information, contact Aleme Tadesse at catchaleme@gmail.com or call +1 (202) 45-3117. Together, let\'s empower young people, foster creativity, and embrace our cultural heritage through the arts. ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ Urgent Space Needed for Weekly Painting Sessions - Beteseb African Heritage Art Center Attention Community Members, Beteseb African Heritage Art Center, a startup non-profit organization dedicated to fostering art, cultural heritage, and community engagement, is in urgent need of a space to host our weekly painting sessions for kids and adults. With nine years of experience organizing painting events, we have witnessed the transformative power of art. These sessions provide a nurturing environment for artistic expression and personal growth. We are reaching out to our community for immediate assistance in finding a suitable venue for our painting sessions. The space is urgently needed to accommodate our upcoming sessions. We are looking for a location that offers: Sufficient room for group gatherings Art-friendly environment with natural light and good ventilation Accessibility by public transportation and parking facilities Basic amenities such as tables, chairs, and restrooms By providing a space, you would greatly contribute to the growth of our startup non-profit andsupport the arts within our community. We are more than willing to acknowledge your generous support through our marketing efforts and social media channels. If you have any available spaces or suggestions, we kindly request you to reach out to us at catchaleme@gmail.com. Your prompt assistance in this matter would be highly appreciated. Thank you for your support in helping us create an inclusive and vibrant artistic space for our community. Warm regards, Beteseb African Heritage Art Center (Startup Non-Profit) . ', '2023-06-13 02:39:52', 'c2ca4527f23d36d096eaa09d06ada84e', 1, 1, 1, '*', '2023-04-04 03:55:31', NULL, '2023-04-04 03:55:31', NULL, 0, 0, 3, );
